itl.enabler.api

Class TerminalCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • itl.enabler.api.TerminalCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Terminal>

    public class TerminalCollection
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Terminal>
    A collection of Terminal objects

    Note : The collection of Terminals can be iterated with the foreach statement or accessed directly by its index or by the Terminal Id key.
    Events for all the Terminals can also be accessed via this collection

    See Also:
    Terminal

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static interface  TerminalCollection.TerminalCollectionEventListener
      Listens to events from every Terminal in the collection.
      Clients can either implement this interface to receive events on the whole Terminal Collection or subscribe to events from individual terminalsByNum.
